The '''High Speed Rail (Preparation) Act 2013''' is an [[Acts of Parliament in the United Kingdom|Act of Parliament]] in the [[United Kingdom]] which allows expenditure on essential preparatory work, including construction design, on Phase One and Phase Two of HS2 and all future phases of a high speed rail network.<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.gov.uk/government/news/major-milestone-for-hs2-as-first-piece-of-legislation-receives-go-ahead | publisher = UK Government| title = HS2 bill passed | date = 21 November 2013 | accessdate = 1 May 2014 }}</ref> The Act was the first stage in constructing [[High Speed 2]].

The [[High Speed Rail (London – West Midlands) Act 2017|Hybrid Bill]] enabling Phase One of the project received Royal Assent on 3 February 2017.

